To confirm the nature of the ϕpin transition, we show here that Vbi indeed becomes pinned at ϕpin. We obtained Vbi from Voc measurements at 1 sun, and below 150 K where shutdown of carrier injection leaves photocurrent to freely track the direction of the internal field, which reverses at the flatband condition10,33. Figure 3 shows the Voc (ϕ) plots for selected temperatures. Vbi exhibits a temperature dependence of the form: Vbi = Vo − βT, where Vo is the zero-K term and β is of the order of a few k/e10. β receives contributions from the temperature dependences of bandgap and also electrostatic band bending due to the accumulated carrier tail34,35. This band bending has been confirmed by UPS on polymer organic semiconductors36, including monolayer to multilayer stacks of P3HT on PEDT:PSSH37. Lowering temperature contracts this carrier tail, increasing Vbi. Thus the Voc (ϕ) plots below 70 K collapse to a “universal” characteristic, indicating that Vo has been approached within experimental resolution. This characteristic exhibits a unity slope (i.e., dVodϕ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
